cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with the generation and analysis of Internet Autonomous System (AS) topologies. It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category as it discusses the local interconnection structure between ASs. The paper also touches upon issues related to security and cryptography (cs.CR) as it uses BGP data from multiple vantage points. Additionally, it involves the analysis of complex data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT) as it evaluates the effectiveness of AS topology generation models.
